Verification
Step 1: Stage and Commit Files
git add .pre-commit-config.yaml .flake8 .bandit app.py config.json config.yaml
git commit -m "Add pre-commit configuration and sample files"
The pre-commit hooks should run automatically. All checks should pass.

Step 2: Test Hook Enforcement
Create a file with intentional issues:

cat > bad_code.py << 'EOF'
def bad_function(x,y):
    password="secret123"
    return x+y
EOF
Try to commit:

git add bad_code.py
git commit -m "Test bad code"
The commit should be blocked with errors from:

Black (formatting)
Flake8 (linting)
Bandit (security)
Step 3: Verify Hook Bypass (Emergency Use Only)
# This should be used only in emergencies
git commit -m "Emergency commit" --no-verify
Note: This bypasses hooks and should be avoided in production.

Step 4: Check Pre-commit Hook Status
